  <num>24-701</num>
  <heading>Purpose.</heading>
  <text>The purpose of §§ <cite path="§24-701">24-701</cite> to <cite path="§24-711">24-711</cite> is to protect the health and safety of the people of the District of Columbia from the menace of drug addiction and to afford an opportunity to the drug user for rehabilitation. The Congress intends that federal criminal laws shall be enforced against drug users as well as other persons, and §§ <cite path="§24-701">24-701</cite> to <cite path="§24-711">24-711</cite> shall not be used to substitute treatment for punishment in cases of crime committed by drug users.</text>
